description.narrative:
1) Percentage increase in citizens use of courts and Alternative Dispute Resolution Mechanism to resolve disputes;
2) Percentage decrease in case cycle times (Disaggregated by age, gender, physical ability);
3) Number of functional and coordinated administration of justice mechanisms at the national and devolved levels;
4) Proportion of training (to Judicial staff and Judicial Officers) that translates to expeditious delivery of Justice;
4) Percentage increase in knowledge development, sharing and learning platforms;
5) Number of institutional policies that support JTF implementation;

comment.narrative:
1) Low levels of physical and functional access to courts;
2) Inequitable access to justice by Citizen’s; 
3) Limited coordination of the Institutions involved in the chain of administration of Justice;
4) A Judicial culture that is retrogressive and impacts on effective, efficient and expeditious delivery of justice;
5) A Judiciary Transformation Framework (JTF) with aspirations for comprehensive reform of the institution of the Judiciary;

1) Magistrates and Kadhi's Court registry manual adopted in all 110 Magistrate Courts Country-wide;
2) Guidebook on the operations of children’s court completed;
3) Performance management measures adopted for Kadhi Courts;

1) Magistrates and Kadhi's Court registry manual finalized, launched and applied in court registry processes in all Magistrate and Kadhi Courts in Kenya;
2) Access to children courts enhanced through harmonized court access practices;
3) Performance management and measurement understanding signed by all 55 Kenyan Kadhi's and informs case clearance rates.

